content:
As a literature enthusiast, I have been exploring Dylan Thomas' famous poem "Do Not Go Gentle Into That Good Night" and its various literary aspects. I also delved into the historical and cultural context of the poem's writing period and found some interesting connections to Thomas' writing style. Can you help me solve the following code puzzle related to the poem's themes and context?
[PHP code]
<?php
// Code to analyze the poem's themes and cultural context
$poem = "Do Not Go Gentle Into That Good Night";
$themes = array("hope", "despair", "love", "regret");
$cultural_movements = array("romanticism", "modernism", "postmodernism");
foreach ($themes as $theme) {
  echo "The theme of $theme is present in the poem. \n";
}
foreach ($cultural_movements as $movement) {
  echo "The cultural movement of $movement influenced the poem's style. \n";
}
// Code to analyze historical events during poem's writing period
$writing_period = "1945-1951";
$events = array("WWII", "civil rights movement", "space race");
$cultural_movements = array("existentialism", "beat generation", "hippie culture");
echo "The poem was written during the time period of $writing_period. \n";
foreach ($events as $event) {
  echo "The event of $event had an impact on the poem's themes. \n";
}
foreach ($cultural_movements as $movement) {
  echo "The cultural movement of $movement influenced the poem's tone. \n";
}
?>
Hint: Try to understand the poem's message and analyze the connections between its themes and the cultural and historical context of the time period in which it was written.
